What is AWS Control Tower?

Control Tower requires AWS Organizations — it's a hard dependency.

If you try without Organizations:

Control Tower will create an Organization for you during setup if one doesn't exist — but you cannot use Control Tower without Organizations being active.

It is a service that helps you set up and govern multiple AWS accounts in one place automatically.

AWS Control Tower automates the setup of a secure multi-account AWS environment called a Landing Zone. 
It applies guardrails — preventive using SCPs and detective using Config Rules — across all accounts from a single dashboard

Yes, Control Tower is specifically designed for multi-account management. It uses Account Factory to create accounts automatically 
and applies guardrails uniformly across all accounts through AWS Organizations

Simple Analogy

Without Control Tower:
You manually create each AWS account,
set policies, users, guardrails one by one
→ time consuming, error prone

With Control Tower:
Automatically sets up all accounts
with best practices, security policies
guardrails built-in from day one
→ like a pre-built apartment complex
   with rules already in place
------------------------
Real World Use Case

Company has:
  Dev Account
  Staging Account
  Production Account
  Security Account
  Shared Services Account

Practical flow:

Existing account = Organizations — create/invite all 5 accounts, structure OUs
Control Tower — enable it on management account, it registers those accounts and applies guardrails

New account = Control Tower Account Factory. It creates the account in Organizations + applies all governance automatically in one step.

Control Tower:
  → Creates all accounts automatically
  → Applies same security policies to all
  → Centralized logging to Log Archive account
  → Single dashboard to monitor compliance
