To add your friend's existing AWS account into Control Tower, it's called "Enrolling an Account".

Steps to Enroll Existing Account
Console Way

1. Login → Management Account → Control Tower
2. Left menu → "Account Factory"
3. Click → "Enroll Account"
4. Enter your friend's Account ID
5. Select which OU to place it in
6. Click Enroll

Requirements Before Enrolling

Your friend's account needs:

✅ Must have AWSControlTowerExecution role created
✅ Account must be part of same AWS Organization
✅ Not already managed by another Control Tower

Step 1 — Add to AWS Organization First

# From Management account
aws organizations invite-account-to-organization \
    --target Id=123456789012,Type=ACCOUNT   # your friend's account ID

# Your friend must ACCEPT the invite from his account
aws organizations accept-handshake \
    --handshake-id h-xxxxxxxxxx

Step 2 — Create Role in Friend's Account

# Your friend must create this role in HIS account
# Role name must be exactly this:
AWSControlTowerExecution

# Trust policy — allows your Management account to assume it
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Allow",
    "Principal": {
      "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::YOUR_MGMT_ACCOUNT_ID:root"
    },
    "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
  }]
}

Step 3 — Enroll in Control Tower

aws controltower enroll-account \
    --account-id 123456789012 \       # friend's account ID
    --enrolled-ou "Sandbox"           # which OU to place in

After Enrollment

Friend's Account
      │
      ▼
Automatically gets:
  ✅ All guardrails applied
  ✅ CloudTrail enabled
  ✅ Config rules enabled
  ✅ Logs sent to Log Archive account
  ✅ Visible in Control Tower dashboard

